cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on testing smart contract applications, which is a software engineering task. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as smart contracts are used in blockchain technology, which has security implications. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the unique characteristics of the Ethereum smart contract program model. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as smart contracts are executed on a distributed network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the control flow behaviors of smart contracts.
